President Trump expressed optimism about the progress being made in trade negotiations with China during a meeting with Vice Premier Liu He. He stated that a deal between the two countries is getting closer and could be announced within the next four weeks. President Trump also praised China for its recent actions to ban all types of fentanyl, a deadly drug, and crack down on its production. He emphasized the importance of intellectual property protection and enforcement in the negotiations. The President also discussed the possibility of a summit with President Xi Jinping if a deal is reached. He expressed hope that the trade deal would benefit both countries and strengthen their relationship. Additionally, President Trump mentioned the possibility of reducing military expenditures and focusing on long-term peace. He also commented on the nomination of Herman Cain for the Federal Reserve and discussed the situation at the southern border with Mexico.